canvas_summaries.ocr_text: outloiling National Union of Women Teachers 41 CROMWELL ROAD, SOUTH KENSINGTON, LONDON, S. W. 7. Equal Pay for Equal Work. SOME PERTINENT QUESTIONS. 1. Do women teach smaller classes than men? 2. Do they work shorter hours? 3. Do they have longer holidays? 4. Do they show less initiative? 5. Do they work less hard? 6. Do they receive inferior reports from H. M. Inspectors? THE ANSWER IS NO. Justice therefore demands that they should receive Equal Pay for Equal Work. Join the N. U. W. T., the only teachers' organisation working to establish this principle.
